[NPC Narrate] -Jarda looks at you rather suspiciously.-
[NPC Narrate] -His scraggly brows curve down and his lips follow suit, until he looks on the verge of a scowl.-
[NPC Narrate] -It's clear he doesn't believe the fib, and moves his fingers at you indicatively, effectively gesticulating, “out with it.”-
[NPC Internal] Reffitia claims that you share a supplier. People have been getting sick, and I need to know who it is so I can figure out why.
[NPC Narrate] -Jarda relaxes his expression, and he makes a shrug of his massive shoulders before he begins casually wiping the mug out with a cloth.-
[NPC Narrate] -He takes his time with it, watching you as if you decide how much to tell you.-
[NPC Narrate] -When he finishes, he sets the mug down with a thump and reaches beneath the bar to pull out a sheet of paper.-
[NPC Narrate] -He smoothes it carefully for your perusal, and you see that he's been getting his supplies from the same family for about four cycles.-
[NPC Narrate] -The deliveries have been consistent and, judging by the way he's shaking his head at you, he's never had any issue with quality.-
[NPC Internal] Has anyone come in here offering you a deal on cheaper goods?
[NPC Narrate] -Jarda leans forward over the bar, casually flipping the voucher over to its blank back.-
[NPC Narrate] -He begins writing out a description and explanation, his course letters are bulky but legible.-
[NPC Narrate] -The text reads.-
[NPC Narrate] -Text - Some strange fellow came wandering by the other day.-
[NPC Narrate] -Text - Dwarf, older fellow.-
[NPC Narrate] -Text - He was dressed nicely enough, and looked like he'd been recently scrubbed up and polished.-
[NPC Narrate] -Text - But there was something about him that was…off.-
[NPC Narrate] -Text - His eye kept twitching, and if you leaned in close enough there was a faint whiff of something foul.-
[NPC Narrate] -Text - Like waste. Like he went trekking through the sewers.-
[NPC Internal] Are there open sewers in Amdeneir?
[NPC Narrate] -Jarda shakes his head and shrugs lightly.-
[NPC Narrate] -His gaze finds its way back to the door before he returns it to you, obviously checking to make sure nobody came in while he was distracted.-
[NPC Narrate] -He continues to write.-
[NPC Narrate] -Text - He offered to start selling me herbs at a decent price.-
[NPC Narrate] -Text - More than decent actually, it was downright cheap.-
[NPC Narrate] -Text - I couldn't figure out how he thought to make a profit out of it.-
[NPC Narrate] -Text - I started getting suspicious when he grew more and more agitated at my refusal.-
[NPC Narrate] -Text - Finally, he shouted that I was a dung eating tloke and stormed out of my tavern.-
[NPC Narrate] -Jarda Ynarow leans back again and lounges against the wall behind him, folding his arms over his chest and fixing you with a twinkle in his eye.-
[NPC Narrate] -His hand moves in a vague shooing motion, and then he casually slides the paper back beneath the bar and out of sight.-
[NPC Internal] Thank you for your help.
[NPC Narrate] -Jarda winks at you and returns to his work.-

